- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and dependency parsing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes new methods for training parsers using multiple treebanks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of parsers through the use of multiple treebanks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses different strategies for combining and using multiple treebanks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is unlikely as the paper does not deal with image or video data.
